1.title: Garage Sale Swindle: Vintage Costume Jewelry Turned Into Trendy Ear Cuff
1.plot: Ashley Adams from "Feast of Fiction" is in the business of buying junk at garage sales, jazzing it up, and selling it back to the garage sale owners for more than she paid! In this episode, she buys costume jewelry from a couple named Todd and Carmen. Back home in her craft room, Ashley turns the cheap jewelry into super trendy ear cuffs! Will Carmen want to buy them back?

2.title: Garage Sale Swindle: Toy Horse & Books Turned Into Unicorn Bookends
2.plot: Ashley Adams from "Feast of Fiction" is in the business of buying junk at garage sales, jazzing it up, and selling it back to the garage sale owners for more than she paid! In this episode, Ashley buys a toy horse and two books from an 11-year-old girl named Ruthie, and turns them into unicorn bookends.

3.title: Garage Sale Swindle: Windowpane Turned Into Shabby Chic Chalkboard
3.plot: Ashley Adams from "Feast of Fiction" is in the business of buying junk at garage sales, jazzing it up, and selling it back to the garage sale owners for more than she paid! In this episode, Ashley buys a windowpane a moving sale from a man named Cyrus, and turns it into a trendy shabby chic windowpane chalkboard!

4.title: Garage Sale Swindle: Old CD Cases Turned Into Modern Wall Art
4.plot: Ashley Adams from "Feast of Fiction" is in the business of buying junk at garage sales, jazzing it up, and selling it back to the garage sale owners for more than she paid! In this episode, she buys old CDs from a guy named Kyle, and back home in her craft room she uses the old CD cases to create a rad, modern art piece! But, will Kyle buy it back from her?

5.title: Garage Sale Swindle: Lazy Susan & Trash Basket Into Modern Side Table
5.plot: Ashley Adams from "Feast of Fiction" is in the business of buying junk at garage sales, jazzing it up, and selling it back to the garage sale owners for more than she paid! In this episode she buys a Lazy Susan and a Chevron Trash Basket from a woman in Santa Monica named Mindy, and turns it into slick, modern side table! But will Mindy be impressed? Also, Ashley meets the new Garage Sale Swindle mascot dog, who she affectionately names Bargain.

6.title: Garage Sale Swindle: Generic Folding Chairs Into Trendy Craft Chairs
6.plot: Ashley Adams from "Feast of Fiction" is in the business of buying junk at garage sales, jazzing it up, and selling it back to the garage sale owners for more than she paid! In this episode, she visits a sale featuring office liquidation items. So, Ashley puts together a plan to turn two boring, old, & generic office folding chairs into modern, trendy craft chairs fit for any occasion. But will the garage seller, Chrissie, be impressed with the transformation?

7.title: Garage Sale Swindle: Vintage Drawer Into Stylish Jewelry Organizer
7.plot: Ashley Adams from "Feast of Fiction" is in the business of buying junk at garage sales, jazzing it up, and selling it back to the garage sale owners for more than she paid! In this episode, Ashley turns a vintage table drawer into a rad, stylish, and modern jewelry organizer. But will the garage sale owner, Mr. Dennis, buy it back from Ashley for his daughter, Dominique? Or is Dennis a menace to Ashley's perfect record for buy backs this season?

8.title: Garage Sale Swindle: Mason Jar Lids Into Cosmic Coasters
8.plot: Ashley Adams from "Feast of Fiction" is in the business of buying junk at garage sales, jazzing it up, and selling it back to the garage sale owners for more than she paid! After getting turned down by Mr. Dennis at her last garage sale visit, Ashley is looking to get her mojo back. Ironically, the woman in charge at this estate sale, Lauren Serna, is a metaphysical instructor, and she offers to restore Ashley's balance and harmony. So, will the stars align as Ashley attempts to turn Mason Jar Lids into the coolest Cosmic Coasters in all of the galaxy?

imdb.plot outline: Inspired by Pinterest and using her imagination, Ashley Adams ("Feast of Fiction") aims to buy items at a garage sale, re-make them into something completely on-trend, tasteful, and clever, and sell the items back to the garage sale owners for more than she originally paid, making great friends along the way.
